  "prompt": "I have anxiety and depression; was diagnosed less than a year ago. I recently went through a break up... How can I get myself to do things I like?",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions that might help:\n\n1. Start small\n- Break activities into tiny, manageable steps\n- Set very low expectations initially\n- Celebrate even minor accomplishments\n\n2. Be gentle with yourself\n- Understand that healing takes time\n- Don't judge yourself harshly\n- Practice self-compassion\n\n3. Practical strategies\n- Create a basic routine\n- Use accountability methods (like telling a friend)\n- Set a timer for short periods of activity\n- Use positive reinforcement\n- Consider rewards for completing tasks\n\n4. Mental health support\n- Continue therapy if possible\n- Stay consistent with medications\n- Consider support groups\n- Practice mindfulness or meditation\n\n5. Specific activity motivation\n- Choose low-pressure activities\n- Start with things you used to enjoy\n- Try new hobbies that feel low-stress\n- Do activities with supportive friends\n\n6. Physical health\n- Maintain basic self-care\n- Get some light exercise\n- Ensure regular sleep\n- Eat nutritionally\n\nRemember:\n- Progress isn't linear\n- It's okay to have bad days\n- Your feelings are valid\n- Recovery takes time\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these suggestions?",
